para_trans: Regarding administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report (DPR) submitted by the local bodies for the works to be taken up out of the prize money received under Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0.
Tivas Nagar Panchayat, District Amravati.
Government of Maharashtra
Department of Environment and Climate Change
Government Decision No: MAW A0825 / P.No.59 (46) / T.H.2
Martyr Rajguru Chowk, Madam Cama Marg,
Mantralaya, Mumbai 400032
Date: October 15, 2025

Read: (1) Government Decision, Environment and Climate Change Department No. Mission - 2024 / Q. No.66 / T. 9 dated 27th September, 2024 (2) Government Decision, Department of Environment and Climate Change No. Abhiyaan-20219 / P.S. No.57 / T. No. 1, dated 8 HEART, 2022 (3) The minutes of the meetings of the Committee constituted for the approval of the Administrator dated 26th August, 2025

Preamble: My Vasundhara Abhiyan 4. The procedure for the award of cash prizes to the winning local bodies in the 12 categories of the award has been notified vide Government Decision dated 27.09.2024 at Reference No. (1). Accordingly, a Detailed Project Report of the works to be taken up by the local bodies out of the award amount has been prepared vide Government Decision dated 08.02.2022 at Reference No. Administrative approval has to be obtained from a committee constituted under the chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change.

2. Accordingly, for grant of administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report received from the Awardee Local Bodies, Ms. The Committee has made recommendations after discussing the Detailed Project Report submitted by the Local Bodies in its meeting held on 26th August, 2025 under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment & Climate Change. It was under the consideration of the government to grant administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report of the respective local bodies as recommended by the committee.

Government Decision: Considering the points mentioned in the Preamble, the total amount received by Tivasa Nagar Panchayat under My Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0 is Rs. 75.00 The focus will be on the works to be undertaken out of the prize money of Rs. The Detailed Project Report costing Rs.74,49, 070.00 (Rupees Seventy Four Lakhs Ninety Nine Thousand Seventy Only) has been submitted by the Principal, Tivas Nagar Panchayat with the technical approval of the City Engineer, Chandrapur Municipal Corporation. The proposal was submitted by the Tivas Nagar Panchayat. Committee constituted under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment & Climate Change on 26th August, 2025
Government Decision No: MAWA-0825 / P.No.159 (46) / T. A. 1.

It was discussed in the meeting. As per the recommendation made by the said committee, the total amount submitted by Tivasa Nagar Panchayat is Rs. The works in the Detailed Project Report costing Rs.74,49, 070.00 (Rupees Seventy Four Lakhs Ninety Five Thousand Seventy Only) are being accorded administrative sanction by the Government subject to the following conditions and conditions. The works for which administrative sanction is being granted are shown in the accompanying Annexure-I.
3. Terms and Conditions 1) The operational mechanism for the works in this Detailed Project Report shall remain in the Tibsa Nagar Panchayat.

2) The financial and physical progress report of the implementation of the works mentioned in this Detailed Project Report should be sent to my Vasundhara Mission Directorate by the 5th of every month.
3) The implementation of the works in this Detailed Project Report should be completed within the next 6 months from the approval of the Administrator.
4) Expenditure in excess of the prize money should be made out of self-funding.
5) In case of any increase in the original project cost in this Detailed Project Report for any reason, no additional funds / grants will be made available for the same.

4. My Vasundhara Abhiyan 4. 0 to Tivasa Nagar Panchayat for the first position at the divisional level in the category "Municipal Councils and Nagar Panchayat Groups (population less than 15 thousand)" with a sum of Rs. A prize of ₹1 lakh has been received. Of this, 50 per cent is Rs. An amount of ₹1 lakh has been disbursed to them. Since the detailed project report of the works to be taken out of this prize money has been granted administrative sanction by the Government as per paragraphs 1 and 2 above, the remaining amount of the prize money to the Tivasa Nagar Panchayat is Rs. The Government is approving the disbursement of the second instalment of ₹1 lakh (Rupees thirty-seven lakh fifty thousand only) through Maharashtra Pollution Control Board.
5. To make the said Government Decision available on the Government of Maharashtra website www.maharashtra.gov.in.
